 Willowvale - A 19-year-old man is expected in court after he was arrested by Willowvale police for the alleged murder of an 80-year-old woman. "It is alleged that the deceased was stabbed on her upper body on Tuesday, at about 15:40 at Sunduza Locality, Upper Mbhangcolo Village, Willowvale," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "A community member saw the suspect stabbing the old woman. "The eye-witness raised an alarm and community members came in numbers." Capt Manatha said that the suspect tried to flee but was caught and police were informed. "Police arrived and arrested the suspect. The suspect has been charged with murder. The motive behind the murder is not clear at this point in time." He said that the deceased was identified as Nomaka Mhlaba, aged 80. "The suspect will appear before the Willowvale Magistrate’s Court on Thursday on a charge of murder." Butterworth SAPS Cluster Commander, Brigadier Ngangema Xakavu, condemned the brutal murder of an old defenceless woman. He applauded the community members for assisting the police in arresting the suspect. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 